ries.jpg\"/>Helpful Links</h1>\r\n      <p>These links have been compiled to provide you with additional resources related to the building industry and better building practices.<br/>\r\n      <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.peo.on.ca\"/></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hrai.ca\">HRAI: Heating Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Institute of Canada</a><br/>\r\n      </p>\r\n      <p> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cagbc.org\">CaGBC: Canadian Green Building Council </a><br/>\r\n      <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.hpbacanada.org\"/></p>\r\n      <p> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ohao.org\">OHAO: Occupational Hygiene Association of Ontario </a><br/>\r\n        <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ohao.org\"/></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.csa.ca\">CSA: Canadian Standards Association</a><br/>\r\n      <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.csa.ca\"/></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cmhc.ca/en/inpr/rehi/index.cfm\">CMHC Research Highlights\r\n        </a><br/>\r\n        <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cmhc-schl.gc.ca/en\"/></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://cresnet.ca\">CRESNET: Canadian Residential Energy Services Network\r\n        </a><br/>\r\n      <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://cresnet.ca\"/></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.eeba.org\">EEBA: Energy and Environmental Building Association</a><br/>\r\n        <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cpsa.com\"/></p>\r\n      <p> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ec.gc.ca\">Environment Canada</a><br/>\r\n      <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.ec.gc.ca\"/></p>\r\n      <p> <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.epa.gov\">U.S. Environmental Protection Agency </a><br/>\r\n        <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.epa.gov\"/></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"www.lung.ca\">Canadian Lung Association</a></p>\r\n      <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://healthandenergy.com\">Health and Energy\r\n        </a></p>\r\n         <p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.buildingknowledge.com\">Building Knowledge Inc. \r\n        </a>\r\n         </p><p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.enerquality.ca\">EnerQuality Corporation  \r\n        </a><br/>\r\n        </p><p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.cmhc.ca/en/co/co_001.cfm\">CMHC About Your House Series \r\n        </a><br/>\r\n        </p><p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.iaq.qai.com\">CMHC IAQ Program  \r\n        </a><br/>\r\n  </p></div>',5),(10,'extended','','',5),(11,'body','','',6),(12,'extended','','',6),(13,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Introduction</h1>\r\n<p>Welcome to my website that is dedicated to helping the building industry and trade contractors build, renovate and sell more efficient, comfortable, healthier and more durable homes. As a professional engineer, trainer, author and industry consultant for the last 25 years, I have had the pleasure of working with great building professionals across North America who are dedicated to a path of continual improvement.</p>\r\n<p>As in all the training I do, I welcome your comments, feedback and interaction. We are a large and diverse industry &ndash; manufacturers, designers, consultants, suppliers, trade contractors, sales agents, building officials, energy raters, government representatives, builders and renovators. All of us have an important viewpoint on the industry, so please engage in the betterment of our industry by using and responding to the information presented.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you: Gord Cooke</p>\r\n<p><strong>Biography       </strong></p>\r\n<p>For the past two decades, Gord Cooke has been an effective and passionate educator and advocate for better building practices, improved indoor air quality and energy efficiency. He has a unique talent of taking the complex issues of building science and breaking them into easily understood elements with practical real-world applications for all audiences.       Gord&rsquo;s building science training curricula covers the gamut from creating and delivering basic and advanced building science principles through managing indoor air quality to HVAC system design to an intensive sales training workshop. He has pioneered new training programs designed to assist builders in the sales and marketing of higher performing, energy efficient homes -- helping builders more effectively tell their story to customers, increase their margins and sell more homes.</p>\r\n<p>Gord has delivered sessions at such conferences as the NAHB&rsquo;s International Builders Show, Energy Design Conference, JLC Live, West Coast Green and the National Green Building Conference and is an active Energy &amp; Environmental Building Association (EEBA) board member and certified trainer. He authored the Build Comfort Program and provided instruction for both the Union and Enbridge Gas companies. Additionally, Gord has authored and co-authored numerous white papers and research studies related to indoor air quality and home performance issues, contributes a regular column to Mechanical Business magazine and is a certified R-2000 Design Evaluator and Trainer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Recent Training and Project Experience        </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>National Trainer, CMHC&rsquo;s Let&rsquo;s Clear The Air Workshop, Build and Renovate to Avoid Mold, and The 3-Day IAQ Investigators Workshop, Canada Mortgage and Housing Corp.</li>\r\n    <li>Author and Trainer, Introduction of Natural Gas Technical Training, Irving Oil Ltd.</li>\r\n    <li>Co-Author, Air Tightness of Houses and Their Duct Systems Study, Consumers Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Quality Assurance Inspector, EnerGuide For Houses Program, Natural Resources Canada</li>\r\n    <li>Author and Trainer, Technical Sales Workshop for New Home Sales Agents, EnerQuality Corp. and NRCan</li>\r\n    <li>Co-Author and Certified Trainer, Domestic Energy Advisor 5 Day Accredited Course, Seneca College</li>\r\n    <li>Certified Trainer, Houses That Work  - Building Science Workshop, EEBA</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, House as a System Workshop, Enbridge Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Trainer, Building Science Workshop for Mechanical Contractors, Union Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Trainer, Ontario Green Communities Initiative, in co-operation with the Energy Training Centre of Seneca College</li>\r\n    <li>Team Member, Build Canada Initiative,  EnerQuality Corporation</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, Tankless Water Heater Workshop, Enbridge Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, HE Furnace Workshop, Enbridge Gas</li>\r\n    <li>Developer and Trainer, Technical Training Program for Energy Management Consultants, Direct Energy</li>\r\n    <li>Co-Developer and Trainer, First Nations Indoor Air Quality Workshop Series, in co-operation with Turtle Island, CMHC</li>\r\n    <li>National Technical Trainer and Advisor, Broan &ndash; Nutone - Venmar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',7),(14,'extended','','',7),(15,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Mission &amp; Values</h1>\r\n<p>Gord&rsquo;s mission is to help improve the quality, comfort, durability and energy efficiency of new homes in Ontario and North America through education and innovative products.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>\r\n<p>To provide technical representation of innovative energy efficient products to the building industry.         <br />\r\nTo provide products for the improvement of indoor air quality.<br />\r\nTo provide services and support to builders to help improve building practices and meet and exceed building program guidelines.<br />\r\nTo provide technical and sales &amp; marketing training to the housing market and related building industries to lessen the impact of building on the environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Values</strong></p>\r\n<p>Gord VALUES :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The outdoor and indoor living environments. All of the products and services he provides are aimed at lessening the environmental footprint of building houses without compromising health or comfort.</li>\r\n    <li>His business relationships. Gord endeavours to build long term relationships with his clients, based on honesty, trust, good service and mutual respect.</li>\r\n    <li>His staff and associates. Gord strives to strengthen their individual understanding and knowledge base by encouraging professional development, and by providing strong leadership and mentoring to maintain the integrity of his company.</li>\r\n    <li>His reputation. Gord takes pride in being a leader in new building technologies, being easy to work with and for, and in being a first call resource for his clients.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',8),(16,'extended','','',8),(17,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n    <h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\"/>Expertise & Experience</h1>\r\n<p>Gord has a wide range of expertise and experience that allows him to appreciate and respond to a wide range of clients and their issues :</p>\r\n      <p> <strong>Technical Expertise </strong></p>\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li>His formal background in the industry started with ventilation and HVAC systems in both residential and institutional buildings. That led him to the study of indoor air quality and he was the first person to complete the Canada Mortgage and Housing Indoor Air Quality Investigators program. He conducts audits in existing homes for homeowners with serious indoor air quality issues.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>He now trains a variety of HVAC contractors, home inspectors and health officials on how to investigate complex IAQ issues in existing homes in a practical way.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>He has been conducting energy audits and performance testing new homes under the R-2000 and ENERGY STAR for New Homes program for over 20 years, working with large volume and custom builders to identify the most practical solutions for improving energy efficiency and durability.\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>As a young engineer, he helped design innovative ventilation products for schools and homes and more recently has helped government agencies and manufacturers evaluate new innovative technologies for the building industry â€“ including HVAC systems, solar, water heating options and insulation products. \r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>Gord is an active Building Canada team member, helping large volume builders find cost effective solutions to improving energy efficiency\r\n        </li></ul>\r\n        <p><strong>Sales Experience :        </strong></p>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Gord has run a successful sales agency since 1986, always concentrating on developing and growing new markets for innovative building industry products.          </li>\r\n          <li>He relates this valuable experience when training HVAC contractors, window sales agents and especially new home sales agents on the essential sales process elements for high performance new homes and products.          </li></ul>\r\n          <p><strong>Program Development :            </strong></p>\r\n          <ul>\r\n            <li>Gord became the interim manager of the Ontario R-2000 program, Canadaâ€™s leading housing energy efficiency program, in the early 1990â€™s. His experience with leading builders as their energy evaluator helped the program focus on the key elements of a new home energy efficiency program.              </li>\r\n            <li>Gord was also the co-author of a college diploma course on building science. He worked with the college to develop both an in-house program for young students and an out-reach program for industry clients.              </li>\r\n            <li>Since that time, he has consulted with utilities, government agencies and Standards writing committees to help them implement new programs and standards to the building industry.              </li></ul>\r\n           <p>This wide circle of experience allows Gord to appreciate the needs of the widest possible range of clients in the building industry â€“ from manufacturers to homeowners, building officials to trade contractors, utilities to educational institutions. It is Gordâ€™s unique ability to take complex issues and view them from many focal points, always with an eye to finding practical and cost effective solutions, that is of such great value to clients.\r\n  \r\n           </p>\r\n  </div>',9),(18,'extended','','',9),(19,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/profile.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n    <h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\"/>Memberships & Awards</h1>\r\n<p>Gord has achieved a high standard of recognition and respect from his peers in the building industry over the last 20 years. Here is a list of his industry association memberships and some awards he has received.             </p>\r\n           <p><strong>Memberships :             </strong></p>\r\n           <p><strong>PEO - </strong>Professional Engineers of Ontario<br/>\r\n             <strong>HRAI</strong> - Heating Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Institute of Canada\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>OHBA</strong> - 	Ontario Home Builders Association\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>CHBA</strong> - Canadian Home Builders Association\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>CaGBC</strong> - Canadian Green Building Council\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>HPBAC</strong> - Hearth Patio BBQ Association of Canada\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>OHAO</strong> - Occupational Hygiene Association of Ontario\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>CSA</strong> - Canadian Standards Association, Technical Committee for Heating Ventilation Air            Conditioning and Refrigeration\r\n             Previous Chairman of the CSA F326 Residential Mechanical Ventilation Sub Committee\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>CMHC</strong> - Canada Mortgage and Housing Corp., International Housing Technology Transfer Team\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>CRESNET</strong> - Canadian Residential Energy Services Network\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>EEBA</strong> - Energy and Environmental Building Association, Board Member\r\n             <br/>\r\n             <strong>CPSA</strong> - Canadian Professional Sales Association             </p>\r\n           <p><strong>Awards :             </strong></p>\r\n           <p>EnerQuality Corp./ OHBA  â€“ Hall of Fame Inductee 2007\r\n             <br/>\r\n             Energy Evaluator of the Year<br/>\r\nR-2000 Evaluator of the Year </p>\r\n  </div>',10),(20,'extended','','',10),(21,'body','Fckeditor','',11),(22,'extended','','',11),(23,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\"><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" />\r\n<h1>Services Offered</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke offers comprehensive  consulting services to help builders, architects and remodelers continuously  improve their practices to deliver high performance homes. Gord provides  support from the smallest first steps to a complete change in design and  construction practices. He helps you fix problems as they arise and, most  importantly, before they happen.</p>\r\n<p>He has helped hundreds of clients achieve  the goals of building programs such as LEED for Homes, ENERGY STAR for New  Homes, American Lung Association&rsquo;s Health House Program, and others.</p>\r\n</div>',12),(24,'extended','','',12),(25,'body','','',13),(26,'extended','','',13),(27,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\"><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<h1>Site Assessments &amp; Workshops</h1>\r\n<p>As an essential complement to his training services, Gord Cooke offers interactive, on-site workshops focused on identifying key design and construction issues and creating solutions. These workshops are critical to building better homes as they provide the opportunity to bring together diverse stakeholders (site supervisors, sales staff, construction trades, etc.) to discuss key issues and challenges, and provide a forum for identifying and solving problems.</p>\r\n<p>Workshops combine training seminars with construction site walk-throughs. A follow-up report outlines observations made on site, including problem areas, best practices, and a planning timeline for implementing changes.</p>\r\n</div>',14),(28,'extended','','',14),(29,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n      <h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\"/>Performance Evaluation & Recommendations</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Assessments\r\n      </strong></p>\r\n      <p>Design and construction assessments are one of the most important beginning steps to building better homes. Gord Cooke provides expert design and construction reviews to assist his clients in developing a clear picture of current practices, short and long term goals, and a roadmap to achieve these goals.        </p>\r\n      <p><strong>Recommendations</strong></p>\r\n      <p>A home is not complete unless Gord Cooke and his team ensure that itâ€™s performing to the standard to which it was designed. Gord provides coordination of testing and diagnostic services and recommendations in order to provide an essential feedback loop on the end performance of each home. His role is to help you develop a good test plan, make sure itâ€™s being implemented appropriately and help you understand and act on test results.</p>\r\n  </div>',15),(30,'extended','','',15),(31,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n      <h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\"/>Plan & Specifications Review</h1>\r\n<p>An average home consists of 15,000 building components that are put together by over 200 different people from 14 different trades. But a home is much more than an assembly of parts. A home is an interactive system and each of its components must be designed to work together. During a plan review, Gord analyzes the following components with the â€œSystems Approachâ€ in mind :</p>\r\n      <ul>\r\n        <li> 	Foundations</li>\r\n        <li> Water Management Details        </li>\r\n        <li>Walls          </li>\r\n        <li>Roofs</li>\r\n        <li> Insulation          </li>\r\n        <li>Air Sealing          </li>\r\n        <li>HVAC </li></ul>\r\n       <p>Extensive system review, material recommendations and design assistance (followed by proper installation) ensure that each home operates as efficiently and effectively as possible.</p>\r\n  </div>',16),(32,'extended','','',16),(33,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Indoor Air Quality Audits</h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke and his team were among the first in Canada to complete the Canada Mortgage and Housing Indoor Air Quality Auditors training and apprenticeship program.</p>\r\n<p>This in-home investigation service, offered to homeowners in Southern Ontario, is a comprehensive investigation with a full, written report identifying opportunities for improving air quality and ensuring homeowners are breathing the best possible air in the home. The process focuses on identifying solutions that are practical and affordable. Audit services are also available for small commercial buildings so employees can enjoy a healthier environment.</p>\r\n</div>',17),(34,'extended','','',17),(35,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\" alt=\"\" />Specialized Air Quality Testing</h1>\r\n<p>Some air quality problems are the result of complex and often hidden problems. In these cases, Gord Cooke offers, in cooperation with certified laboratories :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Mold Testing</li>\r\n    <li>Volatile Organic Compound Testing</li>\r\n    <li>Combustion Products Analysis</li>\r\n    <li>Particulate Matter Identification</li>\r\n    <li>Material Testing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>',18),(36,'extended','','',18),(37,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n      <h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\"/>Air Tightness Testing </h1>\r\n<p>Unwanted air leakage in and out of houses and buildings is responsible for as much as 40% of the heating bill for most homeowners. In addition, many comfort problems, building failures and mold concerns are related to air leakage. Gord Cooke has both the specialized equipment and expertise to test and solve air leakage problems in houses, duct systems and small commercial buildings in Southern Ontario.</p>\r\n  </div>',19),(38,'extended','','',19),(39,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" src=\"/images/headers/services.jpg\" alt=\"Contact\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n      <h1><img width=\"169\" height=\"233\" align=\"right\" src=\"/images/inner_photos/success-stories.jpg\"/>Energy Audit & Simulations </h1>\r\n<p>Gord Cooke has 15 years of experience in performance testing, energy auditing and energy simulation of houses and small commercial buildings. He is a certified R-2000 design evaluator, air tightness tester and inspector, an EnerGuide for Houses Quality Assurance contractor and an ENERGY STAR contractor. He can help builders, renovators and homeowners optimize energy use in new and existing homes. \r\n</p>\r\n         <p>For more information on how Gord Cooke and his team can help you develop a manageable plan of action to increase the quality and performance of your homes, <a href=\"mailto:info@gordcook.com\">click here</a>.</p>\r\n  </div>',20),(40,'extended','','',20),(41,'body','Fckeditor','',21),(42,'extended','','',21),(43,'body','Fckeditor','',22),(44,'extended','','',22),(45,'body','Fckeditor','<div id=\"header-inner\"><img width=\"980\" height=\"96\" alt=\"Contact\" src=\"/images/headers/contact.jpg\" /></div>\r\n<p><r:snippet name=\"quick-navigation\"></r:snippet></p>\r\n<div id=\"inner_col-right\">\r\n<h1>CONTACT US</h1>\r\n<p>Do you have questions, comments or require additional information?  If so, we encourage you to contact us.</p>\r\n<div id=\"contact_form-box\">\r\n<div id=\"theform\">\r\n<form action=\"\" method=\"post\" name=\"form\" id=\"form\">\r\n    <p><label>Name:</label><br />\r\n    <input type=\"text\" style=\"margin-top: 5px; width: 170px;\" id=\"textfield\" name=\"textfield\" /></p>\r\n    <p><label>Email:</label><br />\r\n    <input type=\"text\" style=\"margin-top: 5px; width: 170px;\" id=\"textfield2\" name=\"textfield2\" /></p>\r\n    <p><label>Comments:</label><br />\r\n    <textarea style=\"margin-top: 5px; width: 320px;\" id=\"textfield3\" rows=\"5\" name=\"textfield3\"></textarea></p>\r\n    <table width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\">\r\n        <tbody>\r\n            <tr>\r\n                <td width=\"25\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"checkbox\" name=\"checkbox\" /></td>\r\n                <td><span class=\"smalltxt\">Yes, I would like to receive information<br />\r\n                on upcomin events and company news. </span></td>\r\n                <td width=\"80\" style=\"padding-right: 20px;\"><input type=\"image\" src=\"/images/b_submit_inner.gif\" value=\"Submit\" id=\"button\" name=\"button\" /></td>\r